article.headline: May's 27 lead Towson over UMass 81-71
article.description: — Christian May's 27 points helped Towson defeat UMass 81-71 on Wednesday night.
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- — Christian May's 27 points helped Towson defeat UMass 81-71 on Wednesday night. May also had seven rebounds for the Tigers (4-5). Dylan Williamson scored 17 points, shooting 6 for 12 and 5 of 6 from the free throw line. Charles Thompson shot 3 of 7 from the field and 5 for 10 from the line to finish with 11 points. Keon Thompson finished with 19 points for the Minutemen (4-2). UMass also got 17 points from Matt Cross. Robert Davis Jr. also recorded 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
